Buchanan Street (vantage point), adjoining the S.W. corner of York Ave. This house belonged to Acker (1898-1907) and later (1917) to Domenico Rorengo. It stands on property that was formerly (1874) known as Hamilton Park. The house is about 75 feet back of the street.

July 21, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

137 to 163 York Avenue, east side, between Buchanan and Carlyle Streets, looking south toward the latter. The first two houses (Nos. 137 and 141) belonged in 1874 to Crabtree; the third house (No. 145) was owned by Birtwistle, and the fourth one (No. 149-151) by R. Hartley. (See Beers's map.)

July 21, 1932

P. L. Sperr
